AIG Sees Texas Flooding, Quakes Costing at Least $200 Million
Emma Orr
ejorr_6
May 3, 2016
8:14 AM EDT
Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsApp
Share on LinkedInShare on RedditShare on Google+E-mailShare on TwitterShare on WhatsApp
Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsApp
Share on LinkedInShare on RedditShare on Google+E-mailShare on TwitterShare on WhatsApp
American International Group Inc. said recent natural disasters, including flooding in Texas and earthquakes in Japan and Ecuador, will cost the insurer at least $200 million.The cost could be as high as $300 million, Sid Sankaran, the chief financial officer for the New York-based insurer, said Tuesday in a conference call.
Before it's here, it's on the Bloomberg Terminal.
